            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "For instance, a true `:LspStop` function (were it to exist) would be a wrapper around `vim.lsp.stop_client()`, like this:\n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_user_command(\n  'LspStop',\n  function(info)\n    local clients = vim.iter(info.fargs)\n      :map(function(name) return vim.lsp.get_clients { name = name } end)\n      :flatten()\n      :totable()\n    -- Just stop the client, but don't disable it.\n    vim.lsp.stop_client(clients)\n  end,\n  {\n    desc = 'Stop a client',\n    nargs = '+',\n    complete = function()\n      return vim.iter(vim.lsp.get_clients())\n        :map(function(client) return client.name end)\n        :totable()\n    end,\n  }\n)\n```",
