            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It's both. `enable()` has overlap with \"stop\". LspStop does actively call `client.stop`: https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/a89bfcfd0e44f898341ac8a80ba83ccf6218bef3/plugin/lspconfig.lua#L279\n\nCommands are high-level and meant to be more intuitive, I don't think anything is gained by this change, and actually is a slight cost in terms of user intuition.",
